WEBVTT

1
00:01:32.389 --> 00:01:33.822
Hmm.

2
00:01:36.427 --> 00:01:38.393
I never really thought
I'd come back here.


3
00:02:02.086 --> 00:02:04.219
- Oh, my goodness!
- Yeah.


4
00:02:04.221 --> 00:02:05.754
You're here.

5
00:02:11.562 --> 00:02:14.263
You look like a werewolf
with that beard.


6
00:02:14.265 --> 00:02:15.597
- Yeah.
- God didn't give you


7
00:02:15.599 --> 00:02:17.432
your father's good looks
so you could hide


8
00:02:17.434 --> 00:02:18.767
under all that hair.

9
00:02:18.769 --> 00:02:20.636
It's good to see you, too, Mother.

10
00:02:20.638 --> 00:02:23.438
Don't be too loud.
Your father is already asleep.


11
00:02:24.108 --> 00:02:25.974
You're as beautiful as ever.

12
00:02:29.146 --> 00:02:31.046
You travel light.

13
00:02:31.048 --> 00:02:33.949
We put most of our stuff
in storage in Oakland.


14
00:02:33.951 --> 00:02:36.918
Oh, you should just get
everything shipped here.


15
00:02:36.920 --> 00:02:38.620
Those places are expensive.

16
00:02:45.229 --> 00:02:47.429
Uh, I'm sorry
about the mess.


17
00:02:47.431 --> 00:02:51.366
I've been having a little trouble
getting up and down the stairs, lately.


18
00:02:51.368 --> 00:02:54.503
But, the entire
second floor is yours.


19
00:02:54.505 --> 00:02:56.938
And I even set up
a coffee machine on the bureau.


20
00:02:56.940 --> 00:03:00.709
Mom, we're here to help you,
not give you more work.


21
00:03:00.711 --> 00:03:03.845
Well,
the bed is ready now.


22
00:03:05.549 --> 00:03:07.082
How is Michael?

23
00:03:07.084 --> 00:03:09.017
Oh, he's much better.

24
00:03:09.019 --> 00:03:12.654
And he's so excited
to have Mike back home.


25
00:03:13.924 --> 00:03:16.291
Yeah, he's so excited,
he can't even sleep.


26
00:03:18.028 --> 00:03:20.662
It was a wedding gift
from my in laws.


27
00:03:21.432 --> 00:03:23.565
Yes, very, um...

28
00:03:25.636 --> 00:03:28.236
Sweetheart, if you ever
need anything else to wear,


29
00:03:28.238 --> 00:03:30.138
you just take a look
in these closets.


30
00:03:50.961 --> 00:03:51.927
Right, Mike?

31
00:03:52.629 --> 00:03:54.062
I'm sorry, about what?

32
00:03:54.064 --> 00:03:55.564
The keys to the practice.

33
00:03:55.566 --> 00:03:57.466
Rebecca will be there
at 9:00 tomorrow.


34
00:03:57.468 --> 00:03:58.734
Oh, good.

35
00:04:01.672 --> 00:04:03.739
I am so glad you're home.

36
00:04:15.853 --> 00:04:20.889
I'm getting the feeling that your mom
thinks we're moving in permanently.


37
00:04:20.891 --> 00:04:23.759
Yeah, I had this conversation
with her ten times.


38
00:04:23.761 --> 00:04:25.727
She just hears what she wants.

39
00:04:27.331 --> 00:04:29.398
Well, at least
your father is doing better.


40
00:04:29.400 --> 00:04:30.999
That's some good news, right?

41
00:04:32.369 --> 00:04:34.936
Uh-huh. Mmm-hmm.

42
00:04:36.306 --> 00:04:37.506
Hey.

43
00:04:41.578 --> 00:04:42.811
Thanks for doing this.

44
00:04:43.947 --> 00:04:44.980
Of course.

45
00:04:47.418 --> 00:04:48.650
Come here.

46
00:04:52.456 --> 00:04:55.257
So, my mom try
and sell you on the bed?


47
00:04:56.393 --> 00:04:58.827
It's so creepy.

48
00:05:00.631 --> 00:05:04.132
It's, um,
no, it's perfect for a werewolf.


49
00:05:05.135 --> 00:05:06.501
Huh?

50
00:05:14.611 --> 00:05:16.978
Oh, sorry.

51
00:06:04.261 --> 00:06:06.228
Welcome home, buddy.

52
00:06:19.209 --> 00:06:20.842
Let's see what we got.

53
00:06:25.382 --> 00:06:26.882
Thank you, Rebecca.

54
00:06:27.618 --> 00:06:30.085
Okay. Now, open up for me.

55
00:06:31.021 --> 00:06:34.155
Okay, how many fingers
do you see?


56
00:06:35.559 --> 00:06:37.359
Two.

57
00:06:38.061 --> 00:06:39.160
Good girl.

58
00:06:41.365 --> 00:06:42.931
Mom, I can see you.

59
00:07:00.083 --> 00:07:02.918
I see the apple doesn't
fall far from the tree.

60
00:07:08.392 --> 00:07:12.627
This is Dr. Ericson's number. You
should schedule an appointment with him.


61
00:07:14.464 --> 00:07:15.897
Are you leaving us again?

62
00:07:16.600 --> 00:07:18.199
I'm only here for the summer.

63
00:07:18.201 --> 00:07:20.335
I'm just taking over from my father
till we can sell the practice.


64
00:07:22.439 --> 00:07:23.972
I'm really sorry, Mike.

65
00:07:26.693 --> 00:07:29.411
We're gonna miss him. 
He's just such a great doctor.

66
00:07:30.414 --> 00:07:31.680
A really good guy.

67
00:07:32.783 --> 00:07:34.549
You must be really proud of him.

68
00:07:34.551 --> 00:07:36.818
- Hmm?
- Your father.


69
00:07:37.688 --> 00:07:38.820
You have his hands.

70
00:07:42.726 --> 00:07:44.593
Roman's lenses came in.

71
00:07:44.595 --> 00:07:46.294
Oh, thank you.

72
00:07:47.631 --> 00:07:49.164
- Have a good evening.
- You too.


73
00:07:58.875 --> 00:08:01.176
<i>Hey, honey. Hey.</i>

74
00:08:02.079 --> 00:08:05.580
<i>Listen, I have
a last minute surgery.</i>


75
00:08:05.582 --> 00:08:08.383
<i>Yeah, I won't be home
until about 9:00.</i>


76
00:08:09.553 --> 00:08:10.819
<i>Mmm-hmm.</i>

77
00:08:11.555 --> 00:08:12.787
<i>Okay.</i>

78
00:08:13.457 --> 00:08:14.723
<i>I love you.</i>

79
00:08:33.377 --> 00:08:34.476
That bad, huh?

80
00:08:35.379 --> 00:08:37.012
I'm sorry, Mike.

81
00:08:37.014 --> 00:08:40.048
I'm afraid the results
of the MRI are conclusive.


82
00:08:43.320 --> 00:08:45.854
No. Come on.

83
00:08:46.990 --> 00:08:51.559
The sounds you hear,
your trembling hands...


84
00:08:51.561 --> 00:08:55.130
You have the same mutation
as your father.


85
00:08:55.132 --> 00:08:57.432
It seems you're
developing it earlier.


86
00:09:04.007 --> 00:09:06.041
How long until
I become like him?


87
00:09:08.545 --> 00:09:10.345
It's hard to say.

88
00:09:12.616 --> 00:09:15.450
But meeting here
won't be enough to hide it.


89
00:09:16.586 --> 00:09:19.054
Your symptoms will
be evident soon.


90
00:09:20.057 --> 00:09:22.190
Disorientation, memory loss.

91
00:09:22.826 --> 00:09:24.526
Visual hallucinations.

92
00:09:25.896 --> 00:09:28.096
You won't be able
to take care of yourself.


93
00:09:30.033 --> 00:09:32.534
There's-there's...
There's gotta be something we can do.


94
00:09:37.441 --> 00:09:40.075
Just... go home.

95
00:09:41.411 --> 00:09:42.944
And tell your family.

96
00:09:44.047 --> 00:09:46.014
You don't need
to go through this alone.


97
00:10:06.603 --> 00:10:07.902
Good evening, Father.

98
00:10:12.309 --> 00:10:14.309
Remember little Tania?

99
00:10:15.712 --> 00:10:17.178
Her surgery

100
00:10:18.482 --> 00:10:19.814
went great.

101
00:10:53.550 --> 00:10:55.116
Mom, I'm gonna need your help!

102
00:10:55.886 --> 00:10:57.318
Come on, big boy.

103
00:11:05.862 --> 00:11:06.895
Get away from me!

104
00:11:08.565 --> 00:11:09.964
Stop, stop, stop!

105
00:11:09.966 --> 00:11:11.800
What are you doing?

106
00:11:11.802 --> 00:11:12.834
Ma! Ma!

107
00:11:12.836 --> 00:11:14.302
Get away! Get away!

108
00:11:15.338 --> 00:11:16.437
Mike...

109
00:11:18.775 --> 00:11:20.175
what are you doing here?

110
00:11:21.244 --> 00:11:22.177
Huh?

111
00:11:23.079 --> 00:11:24.078
Huh?

112
00:11:25.715 --> 00:11:26.948
Huh?

113
00:11:32.255 --> 00:11:33.188
What?

114
00:11:35.759 --> 00:11:36.991
Huh.

115
00:11:55.579 --> 00:11:57.078
It still sounds good.

116
00:11:58.582 --> 00:12:00.949
My mom used to play this
all the time when I was a kid.


117
00:12:00.951 --> 00:12:04.319
Yeah, I got it tuned this morning and I
was thinking of teaching piano lessons


118
00:12:04.321 --> 00:12:07.355
to a few of the neighbors
if your parents don't mind.


119
00:12:07.357 --> 00:12:09.490
Well, I guess it all depends
if they're in earshot.


120
00:12:09.492 --> 00:12:10.925
Jerk.

121
00:12:16.399 --> 00:12:17.498
This is for you.

122
00:12:18.902 --> 00:12:20.301
What's the occasion?

123
00:12:21.438 --> 00:12:24.038
Do I need a reason
to tell you how much I love you?


124
00:12:27.878 --> 00:12:29.177
Lovely.

125
00:12:31.014 --> 00:12:32.680
- Will you help me put it on?
- Yeah.


126
00:12:53.837 --> 00:12:55.503
I'd like to keep my throat, too.

127
00:12:55.739 --> 00:12:57.438
Sorry.

128
00:12:57.440 --> 00:13:00.842
You know, for someone who spends
all day with a scalpel in his hand,


129
00:13:00.844 --> 00:13:02.510
you're pretty clumsy
with this stuff.


130
00:13:02.512 --> 00:13:05.146
Got a good hand on your
bra clasp though, didn't I?


131
00:13:06.116 --> 00:13:07.649
Um, eventually.

132
00:13:10.420 --> 00:13:13.988
Oh, it's so pretty.

133
00:13:13.990 --> 00:13:17.692
Let's celebrate. I got a nice
bottle of Bordeaux from Jeffrey's.


134
00:13:31.975 --> 00:13:33.341
Are you okay?

135
00:13:34.644 --> 00:13:36.110
Why don't you sit down?

136
00:13:36.112 --> 00:13:37.378
You look exhausted.

137
00:13:37.380 --> 00:13:42.417
What? No. Look, I can clean it.
Just give me the paper towels.


138
00:13:42.419 --> 00:13:45.620
You have to do it fast,
before it absorbs into the carpet.


139
00:13:50.427 --> 00:13:52.427
I am not a child!
I can do it myself!


140
00:13:52.429 --> 00:13:53.561
You're hurting me.

141
00:13:57.167 --> 00:13:58.433
Babe, I'm so sorry.

142
00:14:00.437 --> 00:14:03.037
I don't even know, uh...

143
00:14:04.841 --> 00:14:06.040
I'm sorry.

144
00:15:02.332 --> 00:15:03.798
<i>They love you.</i>

145
00:15:03.800 --> 00:15:05.566
You didn't see her face.

146
00:15:07.137 --> 00:15:08.669
She was afraid of me.

147
00:15:11.708 --> 00:15:13.241
I can't do this to her.

148
00:15:14.911 --> 00:15:17.011
I want to do it before...

149
00:15:17.013 --> 00:15:19.280
before it's too late
for me to decide.


150
00:15:19.282 --> 00:15:20.948
You will break her heart.

151
00:15:20.950 --> 00:15:22.350
No. No.

152
00:15:23.586 --> 00:15:26.220
She won't find out.
I'll make it look like an accident.


153
00:15:26.222 --> 00:15:29.891
It's never an accident, Mike.
People always find out.


154
00:15:31.594 --> 00:15:32.727
How would you know?

155
00:15:34.130 --> 00:15:36.130
I found out about my daughter.

156
00:15:37.834 --> 00:15:39.834
She was in pain, too.

157
00:15:39.836 --> 00:15:43.871
Everyone thought I was a heartless woman
for trying to end my daughter's suffering.


158
00:15:44.974 --> 00:15:47.141
They found her
on the train tracks.


159
00:15:50.647 --> 00:15:51.712
I'm sorry.

160
00:15:53.616 --> 00:15:57.251
Your case won't meet the
requirements for the California law.


161
00:15:57.720 --> 00:15:59.420
You need to be terminal.

162
00:16:06.563 --> 00:16:10.465
There is a place
in downtown Los Angeles,


163
00:16:11.601 --> 00:16:13.468
run by a friend of mine.

164
00:16:15.071 --> 00:16:16.604
Her name is Vilma.

165
00:16:17.740 --> 00:16:21.876
All of her clients are dealing
with similar feelings.


166
00:16:21.878 --> 00:16:26.948
I think that you should talk to people
who are going through the same thing.


167
00:16:28.051 --> 00:16:29.350
Group therapy.

168
00:16:30.687 --> 00:16:33.855
Sometimes the kindness
of strangers is the best cure.


169
00:17:12.328 --> 00:17:14.562
What the fuck are
you looking at, buddy?


170
00:17:16.032 --> 00:17:19.333
Oh, Mike, you scared me.

171
00:17:24.741 --> 00:17:26.674
I never understood
what you saw in him.


172
00:17:27.343 --> 00:17:28.576
What are you talking about?

173
00:17:28.578 --> 00:17:30.011
We don't have
to pretend anymore.


174
00:17:31.714 --> 00:17:33.681
I know everything
between you and my father.


175
00:17:53.436 --> 00:17:55.002
What if he gets better?

176
00:17:55.004 --> 00:17:57.805
Why can't any of you accept
he's not coming back, Rebecca!


177
00:17:58.474 --> 00:18:00.408
He's gone! He's losing his mind!

178
00:18:03.246 --> 00:18:04.779
There's nothing
we can do about it.


179
00:18:06.683 --> 00:18:07.782
There's no cure.

180
00:18:10.653 --> 00:18:11.719
There is no cure.

181
00:19:17.787 --> 00:19:20.755
- I think I...
- We were waiting for you, Mike.


182
00:19:21.391 --> 00:19:22.723
I am Piedad.

183
00:19:23.693 --> 00:19:26.460
Three months already,
they started the session.


184
00:19:38.141 --> 00:19:42.510
We need you to sign a non-disclosure
agreement before you can join the group.


185
00:19:43.479 --> 00:19:45.146
We're very discreet.

186
00:19:55.525 --> 00:19:57.391
It'll make you free in there.

187
00:20:08.638 --> 00:20:10.738
You can take it off
when you're ready.


188
00:20:14.444 --> 00:20:15.810
<i>Brandon.</i>

189
00:20:16.612 --> 00:20:18.446
I finally
told my daughter.


190
00:20:19.749 --> 00:20:22.750
We went to see
the game last week.


191
00:20:23.653 --> 00:20:25.453
And I had another seizure

192
00:20:25.455 --> 00:20:28.956
and I remember looking
at her face at one point,


193
00:20:28.958 --> 00:20:32.326
and thinking,
I know this is my daughter,


194
00:20:32.328 --> 00:20:33.894
but I can't say her name.

195
00:20:39.235 --> 00:20:40.835
I think she understands.

196
00:20:43.239 --> 00:20:45.539
Or not. Who knows?

197
00:20:49.746 --> 00:20:52.613
At least I know I've had
my chance to say goodbye.


198
00:21:02.792 --> 00:21:05.025
Brandon, we are
going to miss you.


199
00:21:17.473 --> 00:21:19.473
You are finally ready.

200
00:21:26.516 --> 00:21:28.716
We have a new guest tonight.

201
00:21:29.886 --> 00:21:31.285
Welcome, Mike.

202
00:21:32.488 --> 00:21:33.888
What brings you here?

203
00:21:36.025 --> 00:21:40.261
I can feel myself getting
sicker with every day that goes by.


204
00:21:40.263 --> 00:21:43.531
I just don't want to rot
in that house with my father


205
00:21:43.533 --> 00:21:47.501
for... who knows how long.

206
00:21:49.405 --> 00:21:51.505
I can't
-I can't end up like him.

207
00:21:53.342 --> 00:21:54.942
I won't let him do that to me.

208
00:21:58.981 --> 00:22:00.247
And my wife...

209
00:22:01.584 --> 00:22:03.951
she doesn't deserve this burden.

210
00:22:03.953 --> 00:22:06.754
She doesn't deserve to suffer
the way my mother has.


211
00:22:08.658 --> 00:22:12.393
Mike, you're not going
to end up like your father.


212
00:22:12.395 --> 00:22:14.829
Because

213
00:22:14.831 --> 00:22:17.131
you two are completely
different people.


214
00:22:17.133 --> 00:22:19.366
I really wish someone
would have told him that,


215
00:22:19.368 --> 00:22:23.204
like a long time ago,
because I didn't want to be a doctor.


216
00:22:24.941 --> 00:22:27.074
I didn't want to work
at his practice.


217
00:22:29.145 --> 00:22:33.814
I didn't want to put my life on pause,
so I could pick up the pieces of his.


218
00:22:38.287 --> 00:22:39.553
And here I am.

219
00:22:43.626 --> 00:22:46.660
You did all those things
because you wanted to.


220
00:22:47.964 --> 00:22:51.131
I don't think you're taking
responsibility for your life.


221
00:22:52.902 --> 00:22:54.068
And until you do,

222
00:22:55.104 --> 00:22:56.237
you are not ready.

223
00:23:02.345 --> 00:23:03.310
Mike.

224
00:23:07.450 --> 00:23:09.283
I think I can help you.

225
00:23:11.087 --> 00:23:12.119
Follow me.

226
00:23:28.371 --> 00:23:31.539
The cover of<i>Vanitae,</i> June '96.

227
00:23:31.541 --> 00:23:34.775
You probably remember it.
I was everywhere.


228
00:23:36.145 --> 00:23:37.378
Wow, you were pretty.

229
00:23:38.714 --> 00:23:42.249
I mean, ahem, you still are.

230
00:23:42.585 --> 00:23:44.485
You're sweet.

231
00:23:44.487 --> 00:23:46.820
A horrible liar, but sweet.

232
00:23:48.724 --> 00:23:51.392
No, keep it. That's how
I want to be remembered.


233
00:23:54.697 --> 00:23:57.498
So,
you said you could help me.


234
00:23:57.500 --> 00:23:58.866
After the<i>Vanitae</i> photo shoot,

235
00:23:58.868 --> 00:24:00.968
I went back to Spain
for a while.


236
00:24:00.970 --> 00:24:04.638
I was the muse of all
the major designers in Europe,


237
00:24:04.640 --> 00:24:06.307
but when I came back
to the U.S.,


238
00:24:06.309 --> 00:24:07.808
they told me I was too old.

239
00:24:08.911 --> 00:24:11.478
A movie producer came to me
and offered me a role,


240
00:24:11.480 --> 00:24:13.781
if I could get rid
of some wrinkles.


241
00:24:14.784 --> 00:24:16.050
Movie never happened.

242
00:24:16.686 --> 00:24:18.385
But I married that bastard.

243
00:24:19.922 --> 00:24:23.724
He kept asking me to lose
weight, to touch up my face,


244
00:24:25.328 --> 00:24:29.763
and one surgery lead
to the next, until one day,


245
00:24:29.765 --> 00:24:33.400
I couldn't recognize the person who
was staring back at me in the mirror.


246
00:24:34.637 --> 00:24:35.970
And he divorced me.

247
00:24:38.140 --> 00:24:40.307
I tried to kill myself
a few times.


248
00:24:40.309 --> 00:24:42.710
But I didn't have the guts
to finish the job.


249
00:24:44.547 --> 00:24:46.213
Vilma told me I was...

250
00:24:46.215 --> 00:24:48.248
I was crying
for the bastard's attention.


251
00:24:48.250 --> 00:24:49.883
Maybe.

252
00:24:49.885 --> 00:24:52.987
Maybe I was. But not anymore.

253
00:24:53.756 --> 00:24:55.189
I want to die with dignity.

254
00:24:58.394 --> 00:25:00.794
That's when I joined the Chain.

255
00:25:02.531 --> 00:25:04.665
Uh, the Chain?

256
00:25:04.667 --> 00:25:09.236
A group of people that operate under
